     The AXA Research Fund supports breakthrough research projects,
     carried out by best-in class scientists around the world

   Thomas Kirkwood

   President of the Scientific Board, United Kingdom

     As a researcher, you feel you have a duty to help. There's nothing
     more rewarding than to actually contribute to changing things, to
     improve the lives of people living with disabling diseases.

   Dr Laura Alejandra Velazquez Villegas

   Ecole Polytechnique Fédérale of Lausanne, Switzerland

     Science is like art inside the laboratory but we need to connect
     with the outside world to make things happen. The AXA Research Fund
     helps us deliver our work to the public to make our work known.

   Dr Christine Wai

   Faculty of Medicine, The Chinese University of Hong Kong

     The AXA Research Fund support goes beyond funding: we encourage
     researchers to disseminate their knowledge for the benefit of all.

